CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1773411078
OL,3,CSee how you compare as women paid less
OL,4,Cthan men in key sectors
OL,6,FThe information and communication
OL,7,Fsector has the largest pay gap, with
OL,8,Fwomen on average earning 30% less than
OL,9,Fmen.
OL,11,FManufacturing has the second-highest
OL,12,Fdifference and it has grown to 29.7%
OL,13,Ffrom 22.6% in last year's report.
OL,15,FFinance and legal activities round off
OL,16,Fthe top three with a 22.1% disparity.
OL,18,FHowever, one sector, utilities and
OL,19,Fwaste, has a 3.4% negative score,
OL,20,Fmeaning that, on average, women are
OL,21,Fpaid more than men.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
